Clover has confirmed that a security guard has been killed at one of its Johannesburg manufacturing and distribution plants. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Clover has confirmed that a security guard has been killed at one of its Johannesburg manufacturing and distribution plants. The company says the incident happened at its facility in Clayville on Thursday morning. Four others have been reported to be injured. READ: Workers to meet Clover management, government Workers were demonstrating against the retrenchment process currently underway at the dairy producer. Over 800 employees have so far been retrenched as part of its restructuring process. READ: Saftu calls for intensification of Clover strike Clover’s Steven Velthuysen said two other guards were injured and hospitalised after security intervened when around 150 striking workers tried to gain entry to the facility. "This unlawfulness and blatant murder cannot be accepted," he said. "Our people are working with the police to identify the workers that were involved in the video footage and we are also in discussions with our lawyers to see what kind of action we can take against the unions because it's clear that they cannot control their members and that is a very dangerous situation."